page.title: 07River Kennet
page.content: and they have to be cut down. The animals which live in the reeds and feed from them often lose their homes or feeding places. There are some{Osprey}which fly over the river every year. Mr. Woolnough usually sees them and he has seen them go over this year. There are lots of wild fowl which live on the river, and in the nearby water meadows. This year there were five nesting pairs of{Canada Geese.}They all had a brood of goslings.There are also{moorhens, coots}and{swans}on the river. There are at least 16 swans on our stretch.
